</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,260,503]" box="[199,1405,296,323]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,296,323]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Distribution.</emphasis>
Rather restricted to western and southwestern Europe. 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1071,297,323]" name="Portugal" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: five northernmost provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,260,503]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,333,359]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Ecology.</emphasis>
Most often collected in grassland and heathland biotopes, and thus far not observed in the littoral zone, dunes nor mountains. In northwestern Europe, this species is mainly found in humid to rather humid forests, and wooded swamps (or carrs) (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M." box="[462,597,405,431]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,260,503]" box="[199,714,440,467]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,440,467]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
10.3 (common). Fairly rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,260,503]" box="[199,584,476,503]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,476,503]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Activity period.</emphasis>
